sentences: Eugene was born to Homer and Apha Eugene on October 12, 1923, and is the youngest of five brothers.
He retired from the Post Office in 1979 and began to pursue his music career full-time.
In 1978, he wrote, produced, and recorded the album West Indies Blues which was initially released by 504 Records and re-released by the Louisiana Music Factory in 2005.

Eugene has played and taught music for more than 72 years, including teaching trombone and dance orchestra instruments at the Grunewald School of Music.
